metadata.name: wolf in sheep clothing
metadata.description:
It wears a downy disguise,  
And blends in with the fold.  
But behind its soft eyes,  
A heart of ice and cold.

It walks among the innocent,  
And hides its true intent. 
A predator inside,  
A wolf with a lamb's bent.

But beware, oh naive one,  
Do not be fooled by its charm.  
For the wolf in sheep's clothing,  
Will do you harm.
